    "body": "@L-F-Escobar What's the command for your previous run? \r\n\r\nThe mechanism of repairing is: Geth will try to find an available state in disk and rewind the chain to that point in case the corresponding state of head block is missing. \r\nIf you were running full sync `--syncmode full` previously, the older state in disk should be found pretty easily after a few minutes.\r\n",
