    "body": "@rjl493456442 I am running full sync mode. I am using geth as a service, here is my service file\r\n\r\n```\r\n## Geth Mainnet service file\r\n[Unit]\r\nDescription=Geth Mainnet Node\r\nAfter=network.target auditd.service\r\nWants=network.target\r\n\r\n[Service]\r\nWorkingDirectory=/home/pi/ethereum/data/mainnet\r\nExecStart=sudo /usr/local/bin/geth/geth --syncmode full --ethash.dagdir /home/pi/ethereum/data/mainnet/.ethash --datadir /home/pi/ethereum/data/mainnet/chaindata --datadir.ancient /home/pi/ethereum/data/mainnet/chaindata/ancient --ipcpath /home/pi/ethereum/data/mainnet/.eth/geth.ipc --verbosity 3 --trace /home/pi/ethereum/data/mainnet/.trace --port 30303 --metrics --mainnet\r\nUser=pi\r\nGroup=pi\r\nRestart=always\r\nRestartSec=15s\r\n\r\n[Install]\r\nWantedBy=multi-user.target\r\nAlias=gethmainnet.service\r\n```\r\n\r\n@karalabe I did not prune the chainstate. Hail to the king, thanks for all your work good ser!\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nLast night the node started syncing again. Thank the gods! My node has been syncing for almost 4 weeks now, never imagined it would take this long. This is the newest model RPI 4b. \r\nI should point out im booting and running the pi from an SSD not a micro sd card. I thought that would speed up the sync but its still a very slow painful process, imho at least. \r\n\r\n![Screen Shot 2022-06-29 at 10 51 01 AM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/26371796/176503310-3a6f0b87-a4c3-4f77-9af4-a1e80dd12d6e.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThanks y'all for the input! Cheers!",
