    "body": "> Only 40 hours? haha thats rookie numbers. I always plan for a week of down time if I have to restart, days if I'm lucky. I had to set up multiple failover servers just in case one of them has an issue and I've been fortunate enough to not have to deal with everything failing at the same time yet. I don't understand how anyone can confidently run these things without failover.\r\n\r\nI must of been one of the lucky ones lol - i've never been down more than 6 hours - this is very long for me.. I was told maybe I need to update my geth version.. currently running Geth/v1.10.23-stable-d901d853/windows-amd64/go1.18.5\r\nalso my geth folder is 1tb - is that normal for windows? thanks!",
